<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1193,1326]" pageId="1" pageNumber="439">
The members of this genus are mostly strikingly bicoloured and with complex body structure. The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[151,338,1229,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Neohydatothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="439" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,338,1229,1254]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="439">Neohydatothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[829,1000,1229,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="439" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Sericothripinae">Sericothripinae</taxonomicName>
by the available keys (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" pageId="1" pageNumber="439" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Tree, D. J. (2009) Identification and host-plant associations of Australian Sericothripinae (Thysanoptera, Thripidae). Zootaxa, 1983, 1 - 22." type="journal article" year="2009">
Mound &amp; Tree 
<number box="[151,211,1266,1290]" pageId="1" pageNumber="439" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lima" box="[226,490,1265,1290]" pageId="1" pageNumber="439" refString="Lima E. F. B. &amp; Mound, L. A. (2016 a) Systematic relationships of the Thripidae subfamily Sericothripinae (Insecta: Thysanoptera). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 263, 24 - 32. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2016.03.001." type="journal article" year="2016" yearSuffix="a">
Lima &amp; Mound 
<number box="[421,478,1265,1290]" pageId="1" pageNumber="439" value="2016.0">2016</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
&amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lima" box="[534,551,1265,1290]" pageId="1" pageNumber="439" refString="Lima E. F. B. &amp; Mound, L. A. (2016 b) Species-richness in Neotropical Sericothripinae (Thysanoptera: Thripidae). Zootaxa. [in press]" type="book" year="2016" yearSuffix="b">b</bibRefCitation>
). The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[706,893,1265,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Neohydatothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="439" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[706,893,1265,1290]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="439">Neohydatothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the anterior margin of the metasternal plate being transverse or with a shallow emargination medially (
<bibRefCitation author="Lima" box="[1006,1259,1301,1326]" pageId="1" pageNumber="439" refString="Lima E. F. B. &amp; Mound, L. A. (2016 a) Systematic relationships of the Thripidae subfamily Sericothripinae (Insecta: Thysanoptera). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 263, 24 - 32. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2016.03.001." type="journal article" year="2016" yearSuffix="a">
Lima &amp; Mound 
<number box="[1190,1247,1301,1326]" pageId="1" pageNumber="439" value="2016.0">2016</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
&amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lima" box="[1290,1306,1301,1326]" pageId="1" pageNumber="439" refString="Lima E. F. B. &amp; Mound, L. A. (2016 b) Species-richness in Neotropical Sericothripinae (Thysanoptera: Thripidae). Zootaxa. [in press]" type="book" year="2016" yearSuffix="b">b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
